You can compare by the `size` of the `List` of skills to get the result ordered by the number of skills the `User` has. Define a [`Comparator`][1] like the following.

```java
var res = 
    users
        .stream()
        .sorted(
            Comparator
                .comparingInt(
                    (User u) -&gt; u.skills().size()
                )
                .reversed()
        )
        .toList();
// sorted in descending order of number of skills
System.out.println(res);
```

You could also use [`Stream#max`][2] if you only want the one `User` with the greatest amount of skills.

```java
User res = users.stream().max(
   Comparator.comparingInt(u -&gt; u.skills().size())).orElse(null);
```


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api//java.base/java/util/Comparator.html
